    <section>
        <title>About program validation rules</title>
        <para>A validation rule is based on an expression which defines a relationship between data
            element values. The expression forms a condition which should assert that certain
            logical criteria are met.</para>
        <para>The expression consist of:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>a left side</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>a right side</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>an operator </para>
                <para>The operator defines whether the left side must be less than, equal to or
                    greater than the right side.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <example>
            <para>A validation rule could assert that an admitted date given is before the
                discharged date.</para>
        </example>
    </section>
